<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF4952DF934CCB89F993" box="[151,250,1632,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-164@1.[151,1436,489,1854]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Dorsal habitus photographs of Orthobula species: 1. O. aethiopica sp. nov., female; 2. Same, male; 3. O. arca sp. nov., female; 4. Same, male; 5. O. calceata Simon, 1897, female; 6. Same, male; 7. O. marusiki sp. nov., female; 8. Same, male; 9. O. milloti Caporiacco, 1949, female; 10. Same, male; 11. O. radiata Simon, 1897, female; 12. Same, male. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522679/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF49534E934CCA3FF992" box="[262,332,1632,1659]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–58" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1124,1148]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,158,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-316@9.[151,1436,151,1103]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 54–58. Orthobula aethiopica sp. nov., genitalic morphology of holotype female (54, 55) and paratype male (56–58) from Addis Ababa: epigyne, ventral (54) and dorsal (55) views; palp, prolateral (56), ventral (57) and retrolateral (58) views. Scale bars: 0.10 mm. Abbreviations: AG—accessory gland; BU—bursa; CD—copulatory duct; CO—copulatory opening; EM—embolus; FD—fertilisation duct; RFA—retrodistal femoral apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SBB—sclerotised base of bursa; ST I—primary spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522707" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522707/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">54–58</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6E97654CB52AFF4952DF9384CF21F89E" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="263236C7B52AFF4952DF9384CF21F89E" blockId="6.[151,1437,1704,1911]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4952DF9384CA61F92B" bold="true" box="[151,274,1704,1730]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4953EA9385C94EF92B" authority="Haddad &amp; Jin &amp; Platnick, 2022" authorityName="Haddad &amp; Jin &amp; Platnick" authorityYear="2022" box="[418,573,1704,1731]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiopica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4953EA9385C94EF92B" box="[418,573,1704,1731]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. aethiopica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF49500F9384C9D0F92B" bold="true" box="[583,675,1704,1730]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0FCA57AEB52AFF49500F9384C9D0F92B" box="[583,675,1704,1730]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
share with those of 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4951D99385C88CF92B" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1949" box="[913,1023,1704,1731]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milloti">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4951D99385C88CF92B" box="[913,1023,1704,1731]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. milloti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a broad, semicircular anterior ridge in the epigyne, but can be distinguished by the CD being about twice as long as the width of the SBB, while approximately equal to the width of the SBB in 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4950D093DDC870F8E3" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1949" box="[664,771,1776,1803]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milloti">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4950D093DDC870F8E3" box="[664,771,1776,1803]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. milloti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(compare 
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF49513393DCC8BCF8E2" box="[891,975,1776,1803]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–58" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1124,1148]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,158,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-316@9.[151,1436,151,1103]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 54–58. Orthobula aethiopica sp. nov., genitalic morphology of holotype female (54, 55) and paratype male (56–58) from Addis Ababa: epigyne, ventral (54) and dorsal (55) views; palp, prolateral (56), ventral (57) and retrolateral (58) views. Scale bars: 0.10 mm. Abbreviations: AG—accessory gland; BU—bursa; CD—copulatory duct; CO—copulatory opening; EM—embolus; FD—fertilisation duct; RFA—retrodistal femoral apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SBB—sclerotised base of bursa; ST I—primary spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522707" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522707/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Figs 54</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF49564D93DCCF56F8E3" box="[1029,1061,1776,1802]" captionStart="FIGURES 90–95" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,569,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-169@20.[151,1436,561,1839]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 90–95. Orthobula milloti Caporiacco, 1949, genitalic morphology of female from Nairobi (90, 91) and male from Pugu (92–95): epigyne, ventral (90) and dorsal (91) views; right palpal tegulum, retrolateral (92), ventral (93) and prolateral (94) views; left palpal femur, patella and tibia, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522723" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522723/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">90</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4956EB93DDCE48F8E3" authority="Haddad &amp; Jin &amp; Platnick, 2022" authorityName="Haddad &amp; Jin &amp; Platnick" authorityYear="2022" box="[1187,1339,1776,1803]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiopica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4956EB93DDCE48F8E3" box="[1187,1339,1776,1803]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. aethiopica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF49570B93DCCEEFF8E3" bold="true" box="[1347,1436,1776,1802]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0FCA57AEB52AFF49570B93DCCEEFF8E3" box="[1347,1436,1776,1802]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
most closely resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4953BD9239C905F8C7" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1897" box="[501,630,1812,1839]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calceata">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4953BD9239C905F8C7" box="[501,630,1812,1839]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. calceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the slightly undulating embolus in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF4956FE9238CE7FF8C6" box="[1206,1292,1812,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–58" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1124,1148]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,158,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-316@9.[151,1436,151,1103]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 54–58. Orthobula aethiopica sp. nov., genitalic morphology of holotype female (54, 55) and paratype male (56–58) from Addis Ababa: epigyne, ventral (54) and dorsal (55) views; palp, prolateral (56), ventral (57) and retrolateral (58) views. Scale bars: 0.10 mm. Abbreviations: AG—accessory gland; BU—bursa; CD—copulatory duct; CO—copulatory opening; EM—embolus; FD—fertilisation duct; RFA—retrodistal femoral apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SBB—sclerotised base of bursa; ST I—primary spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522707" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522707/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Figs 57</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF4957509238CE44F8C6" box="[1304,1335,1812,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,191,1036]" captionTargetId="figure-26@14.[161,1427,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Orthobula calceata Simon, 1897, genitalic morphology of female (65, 66) and male (67–69) from Bagoé: epigyne, ventral (65) and dorsal (66) views; palp, prolateral (67), ventral (68) and retrolateral (69) views. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522715/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">68</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by the shape of the RFA, which is longer and bifid, with a strongly pronounced distal tooth in 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4957C99215CA7EF89F" authority="Haddad &amp; Jin &amp; Platnick, 2022" authorityName="Haddad &amp; Jin &amp; Platnick" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aethiopica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4957C99215CA7EF89F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. aethiopica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF49535C9270CA1DF89F" bold="true" box="[276,366,1884,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0FCA57AEB52AFF49535C9270CA1DF89F" box="[276,366,1884,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF4953359270CAA2F89E" box="[381,465,1884,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–58" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1124,1148]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,158,1096]" captionTargetId="figure-316@9.[151,1436,151,1103]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 54–58. Orthobula aethiopica sp. nov., genitalic morphology of holotype female (54, 55) and paratype male (56–58) from Addis Ababa: epigyne, ventral (54) and dorsal (55) views; palp, prolateral (56), ventral (57) and retrolateral (58) views. Scale bars: 0.10 mm. Abbreviations: AG—accessory gland; BU—bursa; CD—copulatory duct; CO—copulatory opening; EM—embolus; FD—fertilisation duct; RFA—retrodistal femoral apophysis; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SBB—sclerotised base of bursa; ST I—primary spermathecae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522707" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522707/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
), while shorter and hook-shaped in 
<taxonomicName id="E18D4D44B52AFF4951299271C891F89F" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1897" box="[865,994,1884,1911]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Orthobula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calceata">
<emphasis id="14F9EAD5B52AFF4951299271C891F89F" box="[865,994,1884,1911]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">O. calceata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="BEB62A42B52AFF4951B99270CF35F89E" box="[1009,1094,1884,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–69" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,191,1036]" captionTargetId="figure-26@14.[161,1427,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 65–69. Orthobula calceata Simon, 1897, genitalic morphology of female (65, 66) and male (67–69) from Bagoé: epigyne, ventral (65) and dorsal (66) views; palp, prolateral (67), ventral (68) and retrolateral (69) views. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522715/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="361">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
